```ts
const storageKey = `push_token_registered_${currentMember.id}`;
const alreadyRegistered = await AsyncStorage.getItem(storageKey);
if (alreadyRegistered === 'true') {
  hasRegisteredThisSession.current = true;
  return; // Already registered on this device, skip everything
}
```

4. After `registerPushToken()` succeeds and BEFORE scheduling the confirmation notification, persist to AsyncStorage:
```ts
await AsyncStorage.setItem(storageKey, 'true');
hasRegisteredThisSession.current = true;
```

5. Remove the `hasRegisteredThisSession.current = true` line that currently appears AFTER the confirmation notification schedules — it should now be set right after the AsyncStorage write above.

This way:
- First time the app opens after install: registers, saves flag, shows confirmation notification once
- Every subsequent cold start: reads AsyncStorage, skips registration entirely, no duplicate notification

Make these changes in both files. Keep all other logic exactly the same.

